			    XPCE Runtime Licence
			    ====================

1. Product
==========

The XPCE Runtime System consists of the following components:

	bin/xpce	Linked XPCE/SWI-Prolog executable.  Both subsystems
			are compiled using the flag -DO_RUNTIME and the
			sources have not been modified to alter the effect
			of this compiler directive.

 or	lib/xpce4pl.so	Linked XPCE shared library compile with -DO_RUNTIME
			and the sources have not been modified to alter the
			effect of this compiler directive.

	bitmaps/*.bm	Standard XPCE bitmaps.  The XPCE bitmaps have no
			restrictions on their usage or on copying.

	postscript/pce.ps
			PostScript (tm) header file for XPCE.  This file			may only be used in combination with XPCE.

	RT-LICENCE 	This file. This file may only be copied verbatim.

	README.RT	Info, installation instructions, etc.

	Pce		The XPCE X11 resource file.  May be modified.

2. Copying
==========			

The contents of this directory as described in (1) may be freely copied.
Any modification to any of the parts of  this software or its licence is
illegal.


3. Limitations of Use
=====================

This runtime subsystem may  ONLY  be   used  to  execute XPCE/SWI-Prolog
RUNTIME files (created using qsave_program/[1,2].  It is explicitely not
allowed to

    (a) Use any part of this software together with files from the XPCE
    development system without permission for using the XPCE development
    system.

    (b) Distribute programs CREATED on this environment without
    permission for using the XPCE development system.


